How to compile source code and create packages
Get the project from sourceforge.net.
Must be installed on your Linux system: gcc-c++, make, cmake, usbpp-dev, opengl-dev

For creating makefile and compiling of CNC-mk1-Q:
cmake .
make

If You want to create th package (DEB of RPM), must be installed rpm-build or dpkg
and:
for DEB based distributions:
make package-binary-deb

or for RPM
make package-binary-rpm

